"{\n  \"text\": \"This is the third and final part of the 17-day hot compost from vegetables to garden soil. And you can already see how black it is. There's still a little bit of uh steam coming off this, but a smaller amount for sure. And I've been laying the chickens in there, so they've been just messing it up. And as the pile cools down, the chickens will spread it out more. When it's a hot pile, the chickens tend to get less into it because there are no bugs, are no worms, it's just a bacterial breakdown. But as it begins to cool down, you'll begin to find some bugs and some larvae and some worms in there. And that's when they're really gonna scratch it apart and take it all apart and kind of break it up. And I let them do it at this stage because it's just more air, it's just more uh bacterial matter uh mixing its way around, just more of a mix up, and you'll see it real well. This is uh one day after I'd come back and that was completely spread around. And so I've decided to retire it, and this is the final pitch, and I'm gonna be putting it into the worm pile where it's gonna make some tremendous soil that I'll add to my garden. Very excited to do this, and I'm gonna start another pile tomorrow. Thanks, y'all.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" This is the third and final part of the 17-day hot compost from vegetables to garden soil.\",\n      \"start\": 0.24,\n      \"end\": 7.12,\n      \"duration\": 6.88,\n      \"confidence\": 0.994,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" This\",\n          \"start\": 0.24,\n          \"end\": 0.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.24,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" is\",\n          \"start\": 0.48,\n          \"end\": 0.64,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" the\",\n          \"start\": 0.64,\n          \"end\": 0.8,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\"